25 weeks of the greatest opportunity I’ve ever had. What a blessing and miracle the gift of life truly is, and may we never take it for granted. 🤍 

Bump date: Baby Law is now the size of an eggplant! This week I took my last big trip before my due date, finished my registry, and prepped for our baby shower. I can feel my belly growing more and more everyday, and it’s getting much harder to sleep. Overall, the second trimester has been my absolute favorite part of pregnancy. I’ve had so much more energy, and love feeling him kick and move around. My only negative symptoms have been some round ligament & pelvic pain, along with heartburn and acid reflux. Regardless, I’ll be soaking up every minute of the next three months!!

30 weeks 👼🏻☁️
About two more months left until we meet our little angel.
To be completely honest, the third trimester has really been a challenge for me. I felt like I was absolutely thriving in the second tri, and now lately I’ve had a new onset of difficult symptoms. 

I’ve had pretty bad heartburn, acid reflux, nausea, and a lot of aching in my ribs, pelvis, and legs. My insomnia kicks in most nights around 2am and then I’m just wide awake for hours, and left feeling so fatigued during the day.

I feel almost guilty sharing because I don’t want to sound like I’m complaining or ungrateful, but I also find it comforting to know that I’m not the only one facing some of these struggles that come with pregnancy. 

My highlights have been how much he moves around everyday, it’s just so magical to me! (Even when I get a kick to the rib 😅) We also have been working on his little nursery, and planning maternity photos! Everything is just starting to feel so surreal, and we are counting down the weeks until we have him here with us 🫶🏼

I say it often but I really am so thankful to live here, and can’t wait to raise my baby near the ocean- something I’ve always dreamt of.

Around this time last year, I remember feeling stuck in life and felt like everyone around me was moving forward while I was just getting left behind. I was tired of living in my hometown, Zac and I both felt unfulfilled with our careers, and I was disappointed in myself/body because we were battling infertility, and felt like I couldn’t give 100% to my relationships simply because I just wasn’t happy with myself. To be completely honest I really felt like my life was lacking purpose as a whole.

I remember praying to God and asking him to open up a door, and promising him that whatever he had in store for us we would faithfully follow. I started praying this same prayer every day, and later that month Zac received a job offer that would move us across the country, and a few months after that we found out we were miraculously pregnant after being diagnosed with unexplained infertility. 

Suddenly my purpose in life feels so clear to me, and I feel like I was made for motherhood. Now I am thankful for that period of waiting and longing, because I know it led us to this exact season of life that I couldn’t be more grateful for.🫶🏼

Story time: Zac and I met in 5th grade and had the biggest crushes on each other throughout middle school! We didn’t officially start dating until we were 16, and he took me on our first date to a coffee shop for a Ben Rector concert. Fast forward a few years later and he proposed to me in that same coffee shop, and then the next year we got married and played Ben Rector’s music for our ceremony. Now, exactly 10 years later our first baby is due the same week we had our first real date in that little coffee shop! A full circle moment 🫶🏼 life can be so cute sometimes

mornings with my 8 week old💕

I’ve gotten quite a few comments about how my mornings look unrealistic, but I’ve always just been someone who loves and thrives on a routine. The first 5 weeks or so after Dawson was born, I barely took care of myself and noticed my mental health was taking a toll. Now I have found a good morning routine where I can make sure I get to eat, and do basic self care- brush my teeth, skincare, sometimes shower if I’m lucky, and it’s not only made me feel better, but I’ve also been a better mom.

If you’re a new mom and your morning doesn’t look anything like this, it’s totally okay. Everyone is different and what works for me may not work for someone else. I only share these for fun and to look back on one day. As moms, it’s important to take care of ourselves too! Don’t let anyone make you think otherwise🫶🏼
